# Design System Enforcement

Feature screens (`launcher/feature/**`) must not use Material3 or Compose UI primitives directly for product UI.

## Do not import in feature modules

- `androidx.compose.material3.Text`, `Button`, `Divider`, `MaterialTheme.typography.*`
- Raw `androidx.compose.foundation.text.BasicText` for product copy
- Direct `MaterialTheme.colorScheme` access for styling

## Use instead

- Typography: `MonoLabel`, `DisplayTitle`, `RuleText` from `:core:designsystem`
- Structure: `TerminalRule`, `AppHeader`, `StatusBar`
- Actions: `TerminalButton`
- Media: `ThumbnailImage`
- Tokens: `LauncherColors`, `LauncherSpacing`, `LauncherTheme`

## When a primitive is missing

1. Add a new composable under `launcher/core/designsystem/src/commonMain/.../components/`
2. Use design tokens (`LauncherColors`, `LauncherSpacing`, `LauncherTypography`)
3. Consume the new component from the feature screen

## Allowed in feature modules

- Layout primitives: `Box`, `Column`, `Row`, `LazyColumn`, `Modifier`
- Animation APIs: `animateFloatAsState`, `AnimatedContent`, `spring`, `tween`
- Feature-specific composition: `CatalogScreen`, `CatalogRoster`, `GameDetailPane`
